Transcorp Hilton Hotel Plc. Abuja has promoted Mrs. Ebikaboere Seimodei to the position of director of operations.
The hotel according to a statement from the company, also appointed Janet Dakim as the director of group conference and events.
Until her promotion, Seimodei was the hotel’s operations manager.
She becomes the first Nigerian to occupy the position.
The statement said that she would lead the operations team of the 670-room hotel to deliver consistent services.
Seimodei started her hospitality career over 25 years ago when she joined Transcorp Hilton Abuja as a reservations sales agent on the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) programme.
She rose through the ranks and held several positions including reservations manager, front office manager, quality manager and operations manager.
A graduate of Sociology from the University of Jos, Seimodei has been on various Hilton leadership programmes.
Also, the Kaizen Institute of Africa (KIA) has certified her as a Kaizen manager.
Dakim was also the hotel’s group conference and events manager.
She joined Transcorp Hilton Abuja over 20 years ago and has held various positions in human resources, sales and group, conference and events.
A graduate of Federal Polytechnic Idah, Dakim has been on various leadership programmes including proactive leadership course and GC&Emanagers induction.